other_tests.findings: Ultrasounds of her head never showed intraventricular hemorrhage or periventricular leukomalacia (PVL).
Underwent stricture resection and a temporary ileostomy due to necrotizing enterocolitis.
Noelle was intubated and responsive to surfactant, weaning to room air within 1 day.
other_tests.changes_over_time: By day 5, she was extubated to continuous positive airway pressure.
